Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.17,0:01:37.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.31,0:01:44.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wishing to express his feelings,\Nthe young man ran to the opera house,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:46.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...where his former fiancée\nawaited him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.65,0:01:49.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, he is\nnot yet aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.52,0:01:55.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet aware of his father's sordid past, which\nlies concealed behind the broken engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.13,0:02:00.14,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 13:\NHaidee
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.38,0:02:19.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That man\nis a murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.19,0:02:24.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am surprised to see you come\nall this way, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.02,0:02:27.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this spectacle being provided\nas a sideshow to the opera?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.46,0:02:29.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I take it that you\nrecognize this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.29,0:02:34.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, that is the ring\nthat I gave to your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.66,0:02:36.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It had poison\nhidden inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.47,0:02:40.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness, what a\nfascinating contraption.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.57,0:02:44.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear that you were\ntrying to kill even my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.84,0:02:47.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you jest.\NWhy would I do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.04,0:02:49.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.58,0:02:55.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a simple case of that barbaric custom\nfrom Eastern Space known as the "thrill kill"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.92,0:02:57.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count would never\ndo such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.72,0:03:00.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're being deceived\nby that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.42,0:03:03.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count was the one who told us\nabout the threat to Valentine's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.33,0:03:09.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even a foreigner such as myself can expect\nto receive a proper trial, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.27,0:03:13.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. By law, you will\nreceive an impartial trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.70,0:03:18.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing that sets my mind at ease.\NI have a witness to offer in my defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.11,0:03:20.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.28,0:03:23.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who knows\nthe whole truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:29.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heloise?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.59,0:03:34.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard many fascinating things\nfrom Madame and your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.76,0:03:39.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Including things which touch\nupon certain family affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.46,0:03:40.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.10,0:03:44.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like to do?\NWill you arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.64,0:03:50.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:52.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they were\ngonna arrest him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.81,0:03:54.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not to worry,\ngentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that His Honor the\NCrown Prosecutor made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.01,0:03:59.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.08,0:04:01.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to see that hanging judge\nget some egg on his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.65,0:04:05.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It would be best for you\nto return to your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.96,0:04:06.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But l...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.26,0:04:09.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry\nabout me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.30,0:04:21.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think for an instant\nthat this is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.34,0:04:23.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Villefort...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.94,0:04:26.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That man wants\nto ruin me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.18,0:04:29.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it! You're still\nsaying that nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.71,0:04:34.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can sense it. I can feel an evil\npresence in that man's soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.86,0:04:46.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're still worrying\nabout your former fiancée?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.66,0:04:49.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Marquis Cavalcanti.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.90,0:04:51.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By all means, please\ncall me Andrea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.17,0:04:54.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what my father\nsaid to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.44,0:04:57.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but I don't feel the least bit\ngrateful to you, is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.17,0:04:58.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:01.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's always been my dream\nto play at the opera house,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:04.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but using money to\nmake it come true was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:08.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was your own merit that won you\nthe right to that concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:15.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The reason, of course, is that your talent\nhas transformed me into your humble servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.36,0:05:17.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He left you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.79,0:05:21.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that he doesn't even have\nthe courage to try to steal you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.17,0:05:32.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.98,0:05:35.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There were no records matching\nthe requested term...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:38.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...in any of the volumes\nowned by this library.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:39.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.38,0:05:43.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Royal Library prides itself on being the\ngreatest repository of data in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.79,0:05:46.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe that there could\nbe a word that isn't registered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.46,0:05:50.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that the word is on the General\NSecurity Directorate's banned list.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.36,0:05:52.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:55.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Regulations are in place that\nprohibit general readers...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.80,0:05:57.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...from browsing\nclassified topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.41,0:06:05.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you MEAN, you're cutting off\nmy financial support?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.01,0:06:08.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've had a few\nsudden expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.51,0:06:11.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to do about\nthe presidential election?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.75,0:06:14.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm going\nto have to cut you loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:18.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Me... And you...\NAnd Villefort...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:22.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was our dream to climb\nhand in hand to the top of Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:25.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.33,0:06:29.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why pull out when we're a single step away\nfrom making that dream a reality?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.93,0:06:36.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My, um... analysts are telling me\nto quit gambling on you, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.34,0:06:39.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this about those letters\nfrom Edmond?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.84,0:06:44.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, I'm just saying that\nwe all need to watch our step.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.38,0:06:47.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you win the election,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.95,0:06:51.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...feel free to give me\na call.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.03,0:07:00.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excellency, we've established a comm channel\nwith the Seventh Eastern Space Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:10.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was a shameful display last night,\ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:12.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What insolence!\NWho are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.17,0:07:16.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lucien Debray, First Secretary.\NI'm hurt that you don't remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.81,0:07:19.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the spoiled rich boy\nin the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.15,0:07:23.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count of Monte Cristo is the\ntalk of Paris at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.32,0:07:26.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to arrest him\nwithout good cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.39,0:07:28.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's plotting something,\NI'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.62,0:07:29.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can you prove it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.49,0:07:32.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who decides\nwho is guilty or innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.53,0:07:34.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The General Security Directorate\nis stepping in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:39.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They suspect that you're trying\nto file false charges against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.47,0:07:42.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone a little\ntoo far this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:45.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably only a matter of time\nbefore you're suspended from duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.38,0:07:48.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.08,0:07:50.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.05,0:07:55.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I need your advice\non a certain matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.18,0:07:57.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's rare for YOU to need anybody's\nadvice on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.45,0:08:01.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but to beg an elite member\nof the Ministry of the Interior for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.89,0:08:05.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your best friend\nisn't with you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.83,0:08:12.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Victoria?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.20,0:08:14.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madame is resting\nin her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.47,0:08:17.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what to do\nwith your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.07,0:08:22.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's been acting like this ever since\nshe was out in the night air...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.44,0:08:24.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...at the party in Auteuil\nand caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:29.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, that's why I can't\noffer you a suitable welcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:31.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but perhaps you'd care\nto join us for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.69,0:08:32.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.72,0:08:38.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have a little work to finish up, so my daughter\nwill keep you company until I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.13,0:08:43.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you play another little tune?\NFor Andrea this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.80,0:08:46.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I would be honored if you did!\NOh, that reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.27,0:08:53.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Black hole futures?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.74,0:08:58.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, let's get down\nto business, Michelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.05,0:09:02.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,General Morcerf has called\nand made an appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.48,0:09:06.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind about that! Show me the\nultra-high density materials market!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.59,0:09:07.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.79,0:09:09.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.56,0:09:14.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Danglars has accessed\nthe market.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:16.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.\NSell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:18.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:23.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let him eat his fill. We'll make sure\nthat he's fattened up properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.71,0:09:27.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait until the time is right, and then\nleak intel that there are signs...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.58,0:09:30.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...of an impending massive lmperial Forces\noffensive in the Central Galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.48,0:09:34.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, the thought of lining that vulture's\npockets is a little distasteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.85,0:09:39.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Gankutsuou," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.76,0:09:41.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready\nto start?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.93,0:09:44.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.87,0:09:52.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the Mansion\nof State Secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.27,0:09:54.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What IS this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.64,0:09:56.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A database that's under the direct jurisdiction\nof the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.59,0:10:12.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,State search keyword.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:14.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.92,0:10:19.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lucien Debray, First Secretary, class S.\NAccess granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.90,0:10:24.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.00,0:10:26.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.77,0:10:29.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou is the king\nof the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.07,0:10:30.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Which means what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.87,0:10:34.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's ever seen what he looks like.\NHis name should never be spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.11,0:10:38.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those who break that taboo\nmeet a fate worse than death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:39.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that an\nurban legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.08,0:10:45.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth. He appeared on the fringes\nof the galaxy a thousand years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.45,0:10:47.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and tried to gain control\nof the criminal underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:50.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's an invader?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.73,0:10:55.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou is invincible. He controls\npeople by manipulating their desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:57.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, he was defeated\nby fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.83,0:11:01.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In June of the year 4002 of\nthe Louis Philippe calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:04.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he was apprehended\nand incarcerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.54,0:11:05.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Incarcerated where?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.88,0:11:08.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.64,0:11:10.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where was he imprisoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.28,0:11:11.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:14.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby issue\nlmperial Edict 53!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:21.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou was imprisoned\nin the Chateau d'lf.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.66,0:11:23.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What happened\nafter that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:29.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His death was confirmed\non December 23, 5043.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.80,0:11:30.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.07,0:11:33.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was in prison for more\nthan a thousand years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.37,0:11:35.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What was that\nprisoner's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:37.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Man in the\NIron Mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.24,0:11:38.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What was his\nfull name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.74,0:11:40.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Terminate access immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:42.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:43.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can't answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:46.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby issue special provision 3\nof Edict 53!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:51.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His name...\NHis name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:52.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Illegal access!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.39,0:11:54.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Illegal access!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:58.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Enacting article 6, clause 2 of\nthe Secrets Preservation Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.88,0:12:18.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,T-This isn't good...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.35,0:12:22.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know who Gankutsuou\nreally is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.45,0:12:24.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I HAVE to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:30.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Old man Noirtier\nmight know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:31.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who, him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.89,0:12:34.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, he used to be top dog\nin the Ministry of the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.93,0:12:37.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But he also had a lot of enemies,\nand he was brought down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:40.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the assassination\nof the Prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.07,0:12:45.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was a proponent of\npeace with the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.37,0:12:48.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, that's made it difficult for his\nson, Villefort, to move up in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.98,0:12:51.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, all that work\nhas been for nothing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:13:03.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father... You must be laughing at me, a man\nwho's lost both his status and his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:08.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must think it's poetic justice\nfor a man who's spent his career...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.00,0:13:11.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...sending innocent men to prison\nand presiding over merciless trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.80,0:13:16.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That this is my punishment for defying your\nwishes and supporting war against the Empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.01,0:13:20.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and for doing away with\nyour compatriots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.54,0:13:22.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've worked hard\nto surpass you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.31,0:13:25.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To surpass you, who had the power\nto sway government policy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:29.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the slightest idea\nhow hard that was?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:34.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Any idea how hard it was to be your son\nin a world dominated by hawks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.43,0:13:38.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Suspended from duty," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:41.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So what?!\NSee if I care!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.43,0:13:43.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let it\nend like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:48.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just you watch! I'll come back\nfrom this stronger than ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.21,0:14:01.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's been like that\nsince we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:04.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if she's regressed\nto childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.06,0:14:14.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Excellency, are you certain\nthat this is a wise idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:18.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can still attack after seeing how\nthe peace negotiations at Geneva go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.23,0:14:20.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We must strike\nwhile we have the chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.70,0:14:24.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we are to gain the upper hand at the\nnegotiation table, there can be no hesitation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.64,0:14:28.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A victory here will give your poll numbers\na huge boost, Excellency!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:52.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His Excellency,\nthe Viscount Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.90,0:14:56.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to our\nhumble home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.81,0:14:58.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What may we do\nfor you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.34,0:15:01.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I had hoped to\nmeet with the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.88,0:15:05.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count's illness has\nrendered him bedridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.85,0:15:07.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'd heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.98,0:15:10.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let me wish him\na speedy recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:14.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ask that you allow him\nto remain undisturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:18.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At times like this, he will\nsee no one but me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.49,0:15:23.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count has complete\nfaith in you, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.93,0:15:28.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell him to be on his guard\nagainst Monsieur Villefort.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.67,0:15:32.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that he'll make the Count pay\nfor what he did. So he has to...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.81,0:15:36.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You care a great deal for the Count,\ndon't you, Monsieur Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.11,0:15:39.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:45.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am glad that you are concerned\nfor his well-being.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.19,0:15:47.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How long have you\nbeen with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.29,0:15:55.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It has been a long time now. A long time\nsince the Count deigned to purchase me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.20,0:15:57.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,H-He bought you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.80,0:16:03.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was born into the royal family\nof a certain frontier planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.24,0:16:07.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our world is situated between\nthis kingdom and Eastern Space,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.64,0:16:09.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and had prospered from\nthe trade between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.81,0:16:16.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, our good fortune\nwas not to last for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.35,0:16:20.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,War broke out between\nthe Empire and Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.36,0:16:23.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and my homeworld was engulfed\nin the flames of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.33,0:16:27.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father chose to establish\nan alliance with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.26,0:16:33.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He did this because he had heard that the\npeople of Earth valued freedom highly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.34,0:16:37.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And so, reinforcements\narrived from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.54,0:16:42.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father told me that ten years ago\nwas a time of great turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.91,0:16:46.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that he himself had fought\nin several wars of independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.09,0:16:54.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those reinforcements from Earth\nbetrayed my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.29,0:16:59.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They started a rebellion, leveling\nfalse charges against my father,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.96,0:17:02.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...claiming that he was working\nin collusion with the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:06.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father was killed\nas a traitor,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.70,0:17:11.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and my mother and I were stripped of our\nstatus and sold into the hands of our enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.14,0:17:17.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My mother died soon thereafter,\nand I was left to fend for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.71,0:17:21.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was like a\nwalking corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:29.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, until the day\nthat I met the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.43,0:18:10.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I didn't mean to dredge up\nsuch painful memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.63,0:18:14.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a fool, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.67,0:18:16.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My girlfriend tells me the\nsame thing all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.11,0:18:19.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She says I never stop to think\nabout other people's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.34,0:18:23.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I guess she's more like an old\nchildhood friend than a girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.55,0:18:26.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She gave a piano recital at the\nopera house the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:30.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"It's a wonderful thing to be able\nto express yourself that way."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.29,0:18:34.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought to myself\nwhen I heard her performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:37.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mademoiselle Haidee, you yourself\nare good at the harp, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.33,0:18:42.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please do my family the honor\nof paying us a visit sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.50,0:18:46.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to introduce\nmy friends to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:53.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The night we arrived in Paris, the\NCount said the following to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.71,0:18:58.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Haidee, this is a land where freedom\nand human rights are appreciated."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.25,0:19:04.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"You should do as you wish, acting\naccording to your own free will."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.65,0:19:07.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the way\nthat I see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.66,0:19:13.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I remain here voluntarily, I am here\nbecause I freely choose to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.58,0:19:34.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our young Viscount is one\nlighthearted kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.58,0:19:38.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know? In spite of the fact that there's\na fire lit under his old man's ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.19,0:19:39.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:43.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"It's a wonderful thing to be able\nto express yourself that way."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.56,0:19:46.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna puke!\NThat's so damn pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.76,0:19:50.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are\ntwo of a kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:53.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can see what you really think,\nplain as day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:55.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.\NI don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.60,0:19:59.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You hate him, don't you?!\NYou wanna rip him to pieces, don't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:01.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's have ourselves\nsome fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:03.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take your hands\noff her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.28,0:20:09.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.15,0:20:12.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:17.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.47,0:20:30.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Villefort?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.01,0:20:38.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I cast away all of the horrible feelings\nwithin myself after I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.78,0:20:40.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.08,0:20:47.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And I thought that if I could only\nease your cruel resolve...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.26,0:20:52.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I... I was unable\nto forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.56,0:20:56.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I could not forget how I felt\nwhen I swore revenge that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.97,0:21:05.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Considering how I myself feel, it was wrong\nof me to hope to change how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.45,0:21:15.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.22,0:21:22.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I caused you a great disservice the other day\nby jumping to conclusions as I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.09,0:21:27.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As an apology for my impolite\nbehavior, please... Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.30,0:21:29.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.03,0:23:15.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The person I was in the past\nis not the person that I am today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.30,0:23:19.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who we were in the past\nis not who we are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.91,0:23:22.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo act 14:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.63,0:23:23.04,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 14:\NLost Souls
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.84,0:23:24.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Lost Souls."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.21,0:23:26.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
